I

IObserver - Interface in observerpattern
This interface should be implemented by any class (and therefore object) that wishes to "observe" a "subject" object and respond to notifications that the state of the subject object has been changed.
ISubject - Interface in observerpattern
This interface must be implemented by any class (and therefore object) that will be the "subject" to be "observed" by another object.
ISubjectImpl - Class in observerpattern
This class provides a concrete implementation of the ISubject interface.
ISubjectImpl() - Constructor for class observerpattern.ISubjectImpl
Default constructor required for serialisation, builds "empty" object
